snippet.textDisplay:
I’m not sure where this myth came about but racism has nothing to do with a power position. That is not the definition unless you dig for some “woke” bullshit with a narrative. The simple and accepted definition is: a person who shows or feels discrimination or prejudice against people of other races, or who believes that a particular race is superior to another.
Therefore anyone can be racist.

snippet.textDisplay: Ugh these comments are so disappointing. If your biggest problem with this video is that some of these black people try to make a distinction between systemic oppression and personal view and failed at it, YOU MISSED THE POINT. Obviously black people can be racist, just not against white people because there aren't any institutions/policies set up to oppress them, but for literally every other group that is the case because of a white supremacists history in this country. Just because Black/Asian/Latinx/Native people didn't make the institution, doesn't mean our racial prejudices can't support their existence. I think it says a lot that most of these comments are interested in calling those black people stupid, than challenging all of the "oh my grandma is racist but I let her have it" folks. DEATH WILL NOT GET RID OF RACISM. All that tells me is that these people aren't really interrogating their own biases, and are happy with their level of racism as it is. The realist person in this video was at 3:00, we need to be checked on our racism, and make the necessary adjustments.
